WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.120 --> 00:00:01.400
Hey, good morning, family!

00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:03.293
I'm excited to be with you all today.

00:00:03.293 --> 00:00:05.693
I brought my best friend, Diana, on here—my wife.

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:10.617
She's the behind-the-scenes person; she's been there answering the emails.

00:00:10.949 --> 00:00:19.067
I brought her on before in a past video but never really let her talk a lot about our life and how we make things work.

00:00:19.564 --> 00:00:29.786
We get a lot of emails from people saying, 'My marriage is falling apart,' 'I'm in shambles here,' or 'My kids are backsliding or going to hell.

00:00:29.786 --> 00:00:41.821
' Email after email, and I feel in my heart it's time to talk about how to put God first place in your home.

00:00:42.554 --> 00:00:50.370
I can honestly tell you all, if you are not putting God first place in your house, you're not going to make it.

00:00:50.370 --> 00:00:56.179
There are nights you don't want to pray and you're just ready to go to bed, but you say, 'Hold on, this is priority.

00:00:56.179 --> 00:01:05.640
' I don't care how tired we are, we're going to pray and go before the Father for our children and seek Him.

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:23.155
Even when we're dead tired, where you feel like you've worked all day and don't feel like doing this, how bad is your 'want-to'?

00:01:23.155 --> 00:01:39.818
Do you want your children to know how to live by faith whenever they get older?

00:01:42.159 --> 00:01:44.607
Do you want your marriage to be strong?

00:01:44.607 --> 00:01:59.379
Putting God first, taking communion daily—we take communion daily and pray together every day.

00:01:59.379 --> 00:02:08.890
We read our Bible and listen to the Word all the time.

00:02:12.226 --> 00:02:19.970
It's so much so that I don't even realize I do it.

00:02:19.970 --> 00:02:34.204
Even as the head of the house, I'm always continually praying, singing, or inviting Him into our home.

00:02:34.204 --> 00:02:57.279
Being a leader, man, being a leader of your home, praying with your wife and your children before they go to bed, anointing them with oil—doing the things you can do as a leader.

00:02:57.279 --> 00:03:22.400
They say 70 to 75% of all marriages with special needs children end in divorce, and 50% of all Body of Christ marriages end in divorce.

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:25.956
Here we are, working together.

00:03:25.956 --> 00:03:37.776
Back whenever I got laid off at the church, I worked there for so long.

00:03:37.776 --> 00:04:01.251
When they came to me and said—because our pastor fell morally and they couldn't afford to keep a lot of the staff on—they eliminated a lot of things.

00:04:01.251 --> 00:04:10.360
So, we stepped out by faith and started doing our business selling online just seeking Him.

00:04:10.360 --> 00:04:31.070
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I'm going to speak to you every single day and show you things at thrift stores; I'm going to show you where to find provision for that day.

00:04:31.070 --> 00:04:45.199
' She quit her job because, as I said, she had a master's degree, finished with a 4.

00:04:45.199 --> 00:04:56.560
0 in college, and graduated top of the class summa cum laude.

00:04:56.560 --> 00:05:03.684
'Yeah, I graduated from university while we had little kids.

00:05:03.684 --> 00:05:18.782
It was really a lot to do, but it was a way we were trying to find the path that God had for us.

00:05:18.782 --> 00:05:32.760
Then we started doing the thrift store thing, and that was the path that God blessed in our life.

00:05:32.760 --> 00:05:44.840
It was just going to a thrift store and finding stuff, and that was our provision for the day.

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:55.045
I remember when it first started, the Lord gave me the idea.

00:05:55.045 --> 00:06:10.324
We didn't have enough money to last us through that month, and Brandon and I were talking about it.

00:06:11.258 --> 00:06:26.100
You were like, "It's the month of May and we don't have enough money to pay all our bills.

00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:42.870
" So I went to God in prayer about it and asked for a miracle or a creative idea.

00:06:47.609 --> 00:06:59.715
He brought to my mind the idea of finding something at a thrift store that would hold a profit and selling it online.

00:07:01.947 --> 00:07:06.034
The Lord really blessed that, and that's how we got through that month.

00:07:06.034 --> 00:07:20.479
The Lord just breathed on little things like that, and that's how we've lived our life: staying in prayer, taking communion every day.

00:07:20.479 --> 00:07:31.085
Whenever you stay rooted and grounded in God, He blesses you in the little areas.

00:07:31.085 --> 00:07:36.360
He's always provided for us.

00:07:36.360 --> 00:07:47.940
If we have a problem or a need, we ask God what to do.

00:07:47.940 --> 00:08:07.479
We tell Him we're at the end of our rope, and He's never early, He's never late—He always shows up right on time for us.

00:08:07.479 --> 00:08:10.146
Even in everything.

00:08:10.146 --> 00:08:21.974
' Yeah, it was that way even like what she was talking about in May.

00:08:37.680 --> 00:08:39.072
It was thousands of dollars we needed to pay our bills after I got laid off from the church.

00:08:44.946 --> 00:08:45.240
I thought, 'God, this isn't fair.

00:08:57.685 --> 00:08:57.897
How are we going to get through this?

00:08:57.897 --> 00:09:13.600
' You can feel sorry for yourself and whine, but that isn't going to get you anywhere.

00:09:13.600 --> 00:09:23.560
God is not moved by your need; He's moved by your faith and by a seed.

00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:30.704
When you have seedtime and harvest, when you sow, you'll reap.

00:09:30.704 --> 00:09:46.650
A lot of people think they're helpless and just sit back, but the Bible says whatever you put your hands to will prosper.

00:09:46.650 --> 00:10:00.889
He gives you the power to get wealth; He never told you to sit back and just let God do things.

00:10:00.889 --> 00:10:08.959
No, He gave you dominion and authority on this Earth.

00:10:08.959 --> 00:10:17.880
So, we don't have a mailbox mentality of looking for a handout.

00:10:17.880 --> 00:10:31.248
We don't say, 'Lord, help us, we need a Holy Ghost handshake today at church; please somebody give us a hundred dollars.

00:10:31.248 --> 00:10:40.969
' I never one time sat there and whined about money because I realized what my Covenant says.

00:10:40.969 --> 00:10:49.287
He said He's never seen the righteous forsaken nor his seed begging bread.

00:10:49.287 --> 00:11:11.860
I said, 'Lord, if you said whatever I put my hands to would prosper and you give me creative ideas to get wealth, you're going to give it to us.

00:11:11.860 --> 00:11:16.498
' I was the one praying and fasting, and guess who He spoke to?

00:11:16.498 --> 00:11:19.180
My best friend.

00:11:19.180 --> 00:11:35.751
She came to me and said, 'Brandon, I have an idea,' and my response back was, 'That's crazy, that's not going to work.

00:11:35.751 --> 00:11:40.910
' But I felt like God told me this.

00:11:40.910 --> 00:11:49.829
When the Holy Spirit speaks to you, it's that still, small voice.

00:11:49.829 --> 00:12:03.976
'I haven't had visitations like you, but I've always been led by that still, small voice of the Holy Spirit leading and guiding me.

00:12:03.976 --> 00:12:25.050
Even when my kids were born, we didn't have money to pay the hospital bills, and we would just believe God by faith that they would be paid.

00:12:25.323 --> 00:12:27.990
He always came through.

00:12:27.990 --> 00:12:32.380
He's never early, He's never late.

00:12:32.380 --> 00:12:55.020
Even in finding provision, I've always tried to be a Proverbs 31 wife, taking the resources we have and making them stretch as far as possible.

00:13:10.440 --> 00:13:11.239
I would go to garage sales for everything—baby blankets, baby bottles—just finding them used because God gives you resources.

00:13:20.695 --> 00:13:25.640
You don't just go buy everything new; you make it stretch as far as you can.

00:13:25.640 --> 00:13:35.480
If you're faithful with the little, He will make you ruler over much.

00:13:41.235 --> 00:13:45.511
We've lived so frugally, buying everything used and going to garage sales.

00:13:45.511 --> 00:13:52.480
It's thinking, "How do I find the best deal?

00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:58.720
Lord, lead me to find that deal.

00:14:10.639 --> 00:14:10.899
" He's always helped me.

00:14:10.899 --> 00:14:22.200
' But it was even whenever you came to me and told me the idea for selling online.

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:45.175
I thought there was no way that was going to work, but I trusted the Holy Ghost inside of her just as much as she trusted the Holy Ghost inside of me.

00:14:45.175 --> 00:15:03.820
It took me humbling myself and saying, 'Okay, I trust the voice of the Lord inside of you, babe.

00:15:03.820 --> 00:15:05.814
Let's try it.

00:15:14.330 --> 00:15:14.495
What do we have to lose?

00:15:14.495 --> 00:15:27.093
' So we had a hundred dollars and went to the thrift store.

00:15:27.093 --> 00:15:42.000
We bought the things the Lord put on our hearts to buy, and we were able to pay our electric bill.

00:15:43.236 --> 00:15:45.270
I said, 'Wow, it worked!

00:15:45.270 --> 00:15:52.319
' So I took another fifty dollars and bought more stuff.

00:15:52.319 --> 00:16:05.634
Every single time I pray, the Lord shows me a shirt or something in the thrift store.

00:16:05.634 --> 00:16:11.342
He would lead me and say, 'It's over off this street; go to this one.

00:16:11.342 --> 00:16:26.249
' I'd tell Diana, 'Babe, I had a vision; if you go into this store, this shirt is in there.

00:16:26.249 --> 00:16:32.924
' I'd name the brand and what it looks like.

00:16:32.924 --> 00:16:38.253
She'd go in looking for the item and find it.

00:16:38.253 --> 00:16:51.680
We'd list it and sell it within a week, and we were able to pay our bills again.

00:16:51.680 --> 00:17:06.885
That's the way we've lived our life for seven years now—living by faith for every single thing and asking for favor.

00:17:06.885 --> 00:17:22.543
'Lord, give us favor with the thrift store owners and favor at the garage sale today.

00:17:22.543 --> 00:17:41.880
' When we go through the garage sales, we go through the rich neighborhoods and ask the Lord where to go.

00:17:41.880 --> 00:17:55.640
You become desperate for hearing Him, and He will start speaking to you on a daily basis.

00:17:55.640 --> 00:18:07.034
Now we teach our kids how to live by faith and believe God.

00:18:07.034 --> 00:18:17.749
We believe with all our hearts that tithing and giving are for today.

00:18:17.749 --> 00:18:30.200
My life is an example of being at the bottom of the barrel and coming out on top.

00:18:30.200 --> 00:18:42.380
This year we didn't struggle like we did being janitors at the church, barely making it.

00:18:42.380 --> 00:18:57.580
There's so much financial stress today, but when you make God a priority, He makes you a priority.

00:19:06.211 --> 00:19:06.828
He is an ever-present help in a time of need.

00:19:06.828 --> 00:19:13.500
You've got to keep your marriage strong.

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:30.360
You've got to make peace a priority in your home and keep strife out, because strife is a cancer.

00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:49.320
When you allow the enemy to come in through strife, it is a major blockage to financial overflow and the flow of the Holy Spirit.

00:19:49.320 --> 00:19:56.679
Make peace and joy the umpire of your life.

00:19:56.679 --> 00:20:04.991
The Bible says where there is strife, there is every evil work.

00:20:07.494 --> 00:20:11.559
We're not always perfect; I come across cranky some days.

00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:27.669
We're just human, but we have decided with all our hearts to make Jesus a priority and stand in the gap.

00:20:27.669 --> 00:20:39.240
Abraham said, 'I'm not going to let any man say he made me rich; only God.

00:20:39.240 --> 00:20:45.994
' God is our source and our provider; He's our Jehovah Jireh.

00:20:47.342 --> 00:20:54.982
We also started doing therapy dogs to help kids with special needs.

00:20:54.982 --> 00:21:01.359
It's a joy to see kids or elderly people get a dog.

00:21:01.359 --> 00:21:11.480
It's been a blessing working for yourself instead of 'working for the man.

00:21:11.480 --> 00:21:14.804
' God gives creative ideas.

00:21:14.804 --> 00:21:20.240
Being willing and obedient, you eat the good of the land.

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:24.319
In both cases, the Lord spoke to her.

00:21:24.319 --> 00:21:46.615
She said, 'Brandon, this is what I believe the Lord has shown me,' and it's been big-picture things that changed the course of our lives.

00:21:46.615 --> 00:21:59.231
I'll get the small-picture things or visions of the future, but the Lord uses her in dreams to give her ideas.

00:21:59.231 --> 00:22:08.970
That's what it should be in a marriage; it's not a one-man show.

00:22:09.275 --> 00:22:14.440
You guys have to be a team.

00:22:14.440 --> 00:22:19.535
It's not, 'I'm the alpha male, hear me roar.

00:22:19.535 --> 00:22:24.240
' You are a covenant joint.

00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:34.451
If it's a one-man show, you're not going to win any games.

00:22:34.451 --> 00:22:40.220
Don't put God in a box.

00:22:49.716 --> 00:22:55.439
A lot of people feel like money can only come through a family member or a friend of the church.

00:22:55.439 --> 00:23:04.845
When you close yourself off like that, you're not open to hearing Him.

00:23:04.845 --> 00:23:11.520
He has no limits; He is infinite and mighty.

00:23:11.520 --> 00:23:15.440
He cares about the smallest needs.

00:23:15.440 --> 00:23:23.451
I've always said, 'God, I'm open to any way you choose to help us.

00:23:23.451 --> 00:23:42.440
' Usually, it's something we can use our hands to do because the Bible says He blesses the work of our hands.

00:23:49.573 --> 00:23:49.787
I journal to God and tell Him my desires.

00:23:52.400 --> 00:24:18.720
It's important to write down your prayer requests because if you only think about the big things, you won't notice that He's been there answering a hundred small prayers throughout the year—like a new pair of sneakers or losing ten pounds.

00:24:34.520 --> 00:24:36.730
If you don't write it down, you'll miss it.

00:24:36.730 --> 00:24:46.986
Every year in January, we set out a list of what we're believing God for.

00:24:46.986 --> 00:24:53.120
It could be a vacation or a house.

00:24:58.560 --> 00:25:00.209
We push as hard as we can to believe for that.

00:25:00.209 --> 00:25:09.965
We put Megan on the list every year—for her to be completely whole and restored.

00:25:09.965 --> 00:25:21.039
We even put down for her to be potty trained; she's getting there, though she still has accidents.

00:25:21.039 --> 00:25:25.540
We look at where we came from.

00:25:25.540 --> 00:25:33.911
We're believing for a new house right now that's bigger and has a special room for Megan.

00:25:33.911 --> 00:25:40.057
Write it down at the beginning of the year.

00:25:40.057 --> 00:25:51.130
For your marriage, thank Him that it will be stronger at the end of the year.

00:25:51.130 --> 00:26:02.125
If you're single and believing for a godly spouse, write down the characteristics and qualities.

00:26:02.125 --> 00:26:08.946
Brandon and I both did that before we ever met.

00:26:09.749 --> 00:26:13.559
I was thirteen when I wrote it down.

00:26:15.510 --> 00:26:30.600
I would pray over him before I even knew who he was—praying that God would keep him pure and on fire for Him.

00:26:35.546 --> 00:26:48.820
I strongly believe the protection I've had in my life was because he prayed over me before he ever met me.

00:26:48.820 --> 00:26:57.617
After we got married, we showed each other our lists.

00:27:05.013 --> 00:27:05.239
I wrote down the personality type and everything.

00:27:15.830 --> 00:27:16.095
I said, 'Father, I'm not settling for an Ishmael.

00:27:20.463 --> 00:27:20.874
I want my Isaac.

00:27:20.874 --> 00:27:40.876
' Interestingly, my parents felt called to move to Fort Worth, Texas, to go to Bible school, and that's where I met her.

00:27:40.876 --> 00:27:46.954
The footsteps of the righteous are ordered by the Lord.

00:27:46.954 --> 00:28:03.475
If it wasn't for keeping God a priority, we would have been divorced a long time ago.

00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:11.851
It hasn't always been easy, but we are quick to repent.

00:28:11.851 --> 00:28:18.488
If I have a bad attitude, I say, 'I'm sorry.

00:28:18.488 --> 00:28:24.440
' I want to have a soft heart.

00:28:24.440 --> 00:28:38.085
The Holy Spirit will rebuke me and say, 'You need to go back and make that right.

00:28:38.085 --> 00:28:42.910
' He's always got her back.

00:28:42.910 --> 00:29:01.249
I'll go to her and say, 'Babe, the Holy Spirit just corrected me on how I talked to you, and I apologize.

00:29:01.249 --> 00:29:09.399
' She's glad He cares about her like that.

00:29:09.399 --> 00:29:16.412
Let the Lord be the captain of your life.

00:29:19.429 --> 00:29:25.093
You drive the car, but let Him be the pilot.

00:29:25.093 --> 00:29:40.767
I refuse to let my intellect lead me because the carnal man knows not the things of the Lord.

00:29:40.767 --> 00:29:50.209
I want to be controlled by the Holy Spirit.

00:29:50.209 --> 00:29:54.679
He will make every path straight.

00:29:54.679 --> 00:30:05.034
We don't have enough time on this Earth to keep making bad choices.

00:30:05.034 --> 00:30:07.260
Every day counts.

00:30:07.260 --> 00:30:16.160
Intellect and thinking you know the way can get you in trouble.

00:30:16.160 --> 00:30:24.610
Knowledge sometimes gets in the way because you feel like you don't need Him.

00:30:24.610 --> 00:30:27.389
That's when things don't work.

00:30:28.564 --> 00:30:35.540
We just wanted to come on today and be real about marriage.

00:30:35.540 --> 00:30:38.240
I hope this blessed you.

00:30:39.273 --> 00:30:44.840
Father, we thank you for every married couple watching this.

00:30:45.485 --> 00:30:49.084
We pray a blessing over their marriage.

00:30:49.084 --> 00:30:54.040
No weapon formed against them shall prosper.

00:30:54.040 --> 00:31:07.1000
Satan, we take authority over you in the name of Jesus and bind you off their homes and finances.

00:31:07.1000 --> 00:31:11.279
Get off their children!

00:31:13.800 --> 00:31:16.360
We are seated with Jesus Christ in heavenly places.

00:31:18.111 --> 00:31:27.120
We command you to bow your knee and get out of our houses.

00:31:27.120 --> 00:31:32.920
We call for healing and wholeness.

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:42.000
If a marriage is in jeopardy, we pray peace and deliverance.

00:31:44.667 --> 00:31:47.505
You are the restorer of all things.

00:31:47.505 --> 00:31:52.951
We call the children home in Jesus' name.

00:31:52.951 --> 00:31:56.456
We take our covenant rights.

00:32:08.909 --> 00:32:09.280
We are so grateful for everything You did on that cross.

00:32:26.794 --> 00:32:27.137
I speak to breast cancer right now and command it to leave in the name of Jesus.

00:32:30.460 --> 00:32:35.345
I curse lumps and call for healing over that woman's body.

00:32:46.872 --> 00:32:50.000
I call ovaries healed in the name of Jesus.

00:32:50.000 --> 00:33:08.100
If you're not able to have a baby, I speak to your womb right now and call it to be filled.

00:33:13.693 --> 00:33:17.873
We know the Word says our vine will not cast fruit before the time.

00:33:56.480 --> 00:34:01.693
We lay hold to children right now.

00:34:01.693 --> 00:34:34.700
If there is a man with a seed problem, we call him to be healed so his body produces what it needs to have a child.

00:34:37.719 --> 00:34:41.491
I speak to that uterus and command it to be whole.

00:34:53.995 --> 00:34:54.226
We stand in agreement for a full-term healthy delivery.

00:34:54.226 --> 00:34:58.495
We believe and receive that.

00:34:58.495 --> 00:35:00.920
We call for better jobs, raises, bonuses, and inheritances.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Great blessing is on their homes.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.100
Well, I feel good with that.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.400
We did good, babe.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.150
Jesus loves you, and we'll see you next time.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.000
Bye-bye!
